os, Constancio, Eleazar, Gerardo, Lino, Luz.","Portuguese and Spanish (<b>Dámaso</b>): from the personal name <i>Dámaso</i>, derived from Greek <i>Damasos</i>, meaning ‘tamer’, a derivative of <i>damazein</i> ‘to tame’. Compare   Damian  ."]}]},{"name":"Bouchard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Marcel, Andre, Michel, Normand, Pierre, Cecile, Gilles, Lucien, Alphonse, Jacques, Alain.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Burchard</i>, composed of the elements <i>burg</i> ‘protection’ and <i>hard</i> ‘hard, strong’.","French: in some cases, possibly also a nickname for someone with a big mouth (in either a literal or figurative sense), from <i>bouche</i> ‘mouth’ + the pejorative suffix <i>-ard</i>. Compare   Buschor  ,   Bushard  ,   Bushaw  , and   Bushor  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bushard","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Bouchard  .","Possibly, in some cases, also an Americanized form of German <b>Buschard</b> (see   Bushart   2)."]},{"name":"Buschor","meanings":["Swiss German: probably a Germanized form of French   Bouchard  . Compare   Buschur   and   Bushor  ."]},{"name":"Bushore","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Bouchard  , reflecting the characteristic Canadian and American French rounding of the <i>-ard</i> ending. Compare   Bushor  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Demoiselle Bouchard De Vichy DE DAMAS was born in 1185, in Vichy, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France. She married Bouchard de Vichy before 1205, in France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1185–":"1185–Surnud","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1205–1250":"1205–1250","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","before 1205":"enne 1205","1205":"1205","1200":"1200","1185":"1185","1250":"1250","1172":"1172","1208":"1208","Vichy, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Vichy, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-